      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're tackling a sensitive topic, but it's great that you're aware of the pitfalls. Here are 5 common racial stereotypes that Hollywood overuses: \n\n1. The \"angry black woman\" trope, where a strong black female character is portrayed as bitter, aggressive, and overreacting. \n2. The \"model minority\" stereotype, where Asian characters are expected to be high-achieving, obedient, and silently suffering. \n3. The \"Latinx as the 'heart' of the movie\" trope, where Latinx characters are reduced to providing emotional depth and warmth to a predominantly white cast. \n4. The \"exotic\" or \"mysterious\" Asian character, where their culture and background are used as a plot device or a way to add 'otherness'. \n5. The \"comically subservient\" stereotype, where black characters are reduced to being the comedic relief or serving as a sidekick to a white protagonist.",
